      "kind": "compound_bug_gate_blocked",
      "summary": "PAETint transfer DIVERGED 184 levels: a green tint (Color=[0,1,0],Intensity=1) leaves the TS output UNCHANGED while FCP tints green. TWO bugs compound: (1) PARAM-LOCATION \u2014 the TS registration reads top-level ctx.param('Red') but the real PAETint nests RGB under a `Color` group (id=1), so it silently uses a WHITE (1,1,1) tint (documented as known in channel-mixer.ts:73). (2) TINT-MATH \u2014 tintFilter is a simple luma*color lerp, but FCP's HgcTint is a HARD-LIGHT two-leg select about luma 0.5.",
      "gate_blocked": "Fixing ONLY the param-location (read nested Color) REGRESSES the sole Tint host Objects__Leaves 22.44->19.29 dB (measured 2026-07-22, then reverted per ROADMAP Rule 2). The buggy white-tint COMPENSATES for the wrong tint-math on Leaves' near-gray tint (Color~0.443). So the two bugs must be fixed TOGETHER: decode + implement the hard-light HgcTint shader FIRST, then switch to the nested Color read. Neither fix alone is net-positive.",
      "next": "Decode HgcTint hard-light two-leg transfer (shader source is in channel-mixer.ts header + docs/FILTER_RE_PHASE2.md 'Tint'), implement in tintFilter, THEN read nested Color, and verify Leaves stays >=22.44 on the GUI gate + the transfer test goes to <=2 levels."
